and Salvation |date=March 5, 2018 |accessdate=March 5, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Critical response===\nOn the [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the series has an approval rating of 47% based on 17 reviews, with an average rating of 5.75/10. The site's critical consensus reads: \"Neither remarkably bad nor impressively well-made, Salvation is stereotypical summer television \u2013 a low-stakes diversion that may pass the time well enough for undemanding audiences without ever being particularly memorable along the way.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/salvation/s01 |title=Salvation: Season 1 (2017) |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |publisher=[[Fandango (company)|Fandango]] |accessdate=September 7, 2018}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the series has a score of 48 out of 100, based on 18 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/salvation-2017 |title=Salvation: Season 1 reviews |website=Metacritic |publisher=[[CBS Interactive|CBS Interactive Inc.]] |accessdate=August 9, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Ratings===\n{{Television ratings graph\n| title       = Salvation\n| no_table    = y\n| color1      = #90B1B3\n| color2      = #800285\n| refs        = <ref>For the first season, see {{cite web |url=https://tvseriesfinale.com/tv-show/salvation-2017-season-one-ratings/|title=''Salvation (2017)'': Season One Ratings|work=TV Series Finale|date=October 18, 2017|accessdate=August 17, 2019|url-status=live}}\n----\nFor the second season, see {{cite web |url=https://tvseriesfinale.com/tv-show/salvation-season-two-ratings/|title=''Salvation'': Season Two Ratings|work=TV Series Finale|date=November 20, 2018|accessdate=August 17, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| bar_width   = 20\n| country     = U.S.\n|-\n<!-- S01E01 -->| 4.897\n<!-- S01E02 -->| 4.279\n<!-- S01E03 -->| 3.870\n<!-- S01E04 -->| 3.613\n<!-- S01E05 -->| 3.613\n<!-- S01E06 -->| 3.111\n<!-- S01E07 -->| 2.905\n<!-- S01E08 -->| 2.905\n<!-- 