ountry. Darius resigns as the president, and puts in motion a plan to ram \"Salvation\" against the asteroid. Jillian is held captive by Bass Shepherd. She confronts him about the destruction of the rail gun, but he blames her because she gave him the information. Harris and Grace look at buying a bunker, but they can't afford it. But in a meeting, Harris finds out he may be able to save Grace and Zoe. Darius makes a deal with Nicholas to get his meteorite for use with the EM drives. A problem is found with the rail gun slugs already fired putting in doubt ramming the asteroid. Nicholas requests a meeting with Darius, about saving Grace and Zoe, but instead kidnaps him. Jillian escapes and manages to phone Liam, but the phone dies just as she sees Darius with Nicholas.\n |LineColor       = 800285\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 26\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 13\n |Title           = Get Ready\n |DirectedBy      = Liz Kruger\n |WrittenBy       = Liz Kruger and Craig Shapiro\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|9|17}}\n |Viewers         = 2.61<ref name=\"2.13\">{{Cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/monday-final-ratings-sept-17-2018/|title='Castaways' adjusts down: Monday final ratings|last=Welch|first=Alex|date=September 18, 2018|work=TV By The Numbers|accessdate=September 18, 2018}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = As Harris prepares to launch a nuclear missile at the asteroid as a last-ditch, best-case-scenario option, a badly injured Darius acts on a hunch to prove that their best course of action is to do nothing. Just seconds before the nuke is launched, Darius proves to be correct, leading to a startling revelation for all the Earth.\n |LineColor       = 800285\n}}\n}}\n\n==Production==\n\n===Filming===\nThe first season was filmed in [[Toronto]], Ontario.<ref name=\"filming\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2017/07/11/jennifer-finnigan-salvation-preview-tyrant-cancellation/ |title=Salvation's Jennifer Finnigan Nerds Out Over CBS' 'Fun' Killer Asteroid Drama: 'It's My Favorite Show I've Ever Done' |last=Mitovich |first=Matt Webb |publisher=[[TVLine]] |date=July 11, 2017 |accessdate=July 11, 2017}}</ref> The show relocated to [[Vancouver]], British Columbia for its second season.<ref name=\"filming\">{{cite web |url=http://www.insidevancouver.ca/2018/03/05/filming-in-vancouver-dcs-legends-of-tomorrow-the-good-doctor-spontaneous-and-salvation/ |title=Filming in Vancouver: DC's Legends of Tomorrow, The Good Doctor, Spontaneous, and Salvation |last=Takeuchi |first=Craig |work=insidevancouver.ca |date=March 5, 2018 |accessdate=March 5, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet |user=IanAnthonyDale |author=Ian Anthony Dale |number=975091436768051200 |title=Proof it's not always adversarial. #teamharrius #salvation salvationcbs @ Vancouver, British\u2026 |date=March 17, 2018 |accessdate=March 17, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet |user=MyVancouver |author=TourismVancouver |number=970765998121979904 |title=Filming In Vancouver: DC's Legends of Tomorrow, The Good Doctor, Spontaneous, and Salvation |date=March 5, 2018 |accessdate=March 5, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Critical response===\nOn the [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the series has an approval rating of 47% based on 17 reviews, with an average rating of 5.75/10. The site's critical consensus reads: \"Neither remarkably bad nor impressively well-made, Salvation is stereotypical summer television \u2013 a low-stakes diversion that may pass the time well enough for undemanding audiences without ever being particularly memorable along the way.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/salvation/s01 |title=Salvation: Season 1 (2017) |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |publisher=[[Fandango (company)|Fandango]] |accessdate=September 7, 2018}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the series has a score of 48 out of 100, based on 18 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/salvation-2017 |title=Salvation: Season 1 reviews |website=Metacritic |publisher=[[CBS Interactive|CBS Interactive Inc.]] |accessdate=August 9, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Ratings===\n{{Television ratings graph\n| title       = Salvation\n| no_table    = y\n| color1      = #90B1B3\n| color2      = #800285\n| refs        = <ref>For the first season, see {{cite web |url=https://tvseriesfinale.com/tv-show/salvation-2017-season-one-ratings/|title=''Salvation (2017)'': Season One Ratings|work=TV Series Finale|date=October 18, 2017|accessdate=August 17, 2019|url-status=live}}\n----\nFor the second season, see {{cite web |url=https://tvseriesfinale.com/tv-show/salvation-season-two-ratings/|title=''Salvation'': Season Two Ratings|work=TV Series Finale|date=November 20, 2018|accessdate=August 17, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| bar_width   = 20\n| country     = U.S.\n|-\n<!-- S01E01 -->| 4.897\n<!-- S01E02 -->| 4.279\n<!-- S01E03 -->| 3.870\n<!-- S01E04 -->| 3.613\n<!-- S01E05 -->| 3.613\n<!-- S01E06 -->| 3.111\n<!-- S01E07 -->| 2.905\n<!-- S01E08 -->| 2.905\n<!-- S01E09 -->| 3.126\n<!-- S01E10 -->| 3.442\n<!-- S01E11 -->| 3.447\n<!-- S01E12 -->| 3.508\n<!-- S01E13 -->| 3.126\n|-\n<!-- S02E01 -->| 3.360\n<!-- S02E02 -->| 3.113\n<!-- S02E03 -->| 2.570\n<!-- S02E04 -->| 2.531\n<!-- S02E05 -->| 2.567\n<!-- S02E06 -->| 2.603\n<!-- S02E07 -->| 2.439\n<!-- S02E08 -->| 2.620\n<!-- S02E09 -->| 2.534\n<!-- S02E10 -->| 2.564\n<!-- S02E11 -->| 2.428\n<!-- S02E12 -->| 2.744\n<!-- S02E13 -->| 2.611\n}}\n\n====Season 1====\n{{Television episode ratings\n| title1   = [[#ep1|Pilot]]\n| date1    = July 12, 2017\n| rs1      = 0.7/3\n| viewers1 = 4.90<ref name=\"1.01\"/>\n| dvr1     = 0.2\n| dvrv1    = 1.65\n| total1   = 0.9\n| totalv1  = 6.55<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/dvr-ratings/broadcast-live-7-ratings-for-july-10-16-2017/ |title='America's Got Talent' remains No. 1 in broadcast Live +7 ratings for July 10\u201316 |date=July 26, 2017 |first=Rick |last=Porter |work=TV by the Numbers |acce